criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  be over the age of 18;

          -  have the presence of hemiplegia after stroke;

          -  be wearing an ankle-foot orthosis for at least 6 weeks;

          -  be able to walk independently and comfortably for a minimum distance of 12 m with or
             without assistive aids (AFOs, canes and walkers);

          -  be able to read and understand English, follow verbal instructions and provide verbal
             answers to questions;

          -  be able to reach criterion on the attention task (described below)

          -  be competent to give informed consent as determined by clinical team and noted in the
             health chart

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  have history of balance deficits not related to stroke;

          -  be at high risk of falling during the study;

          -  suffer from severe aphasia or dementia as determined by health chart and/or initial
             cognitive screening using the Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA) test.
